VAR met_kid = false
~ met_kid = true
A kid — twelve, maybe, hard to tell under the grime — presses into the doorway out of the rain when she sees you coming. She doesn't run. That's the worst part. "You're one of them, right? The ones who do things." Her voice is steady in the way that costs a child everything. "My brother went into the warehouse two days ago for Varga's people and he didn't come back out. Nobody'll tell me anything. You're going in there. I've seen you." A beat. "Just — if he's in there. Tell me. That's all. Just tell me."
* [I'll look for him.]
    "His name's Tomas. He's got a coat too big for him. Like mine." She nods, once, and is gone into the rain before you can take it back.
    -> END
* [The warehouse is no place for hope, kid.]
    "I know what it is." She doesn't flinch. "I'm not asking you to hope. I'm asking you to look."
    -> END
* [Not my problem.]
    She studies you for a second, then nods like you've confirmed something she already suspected about people like you. "Okay," she says. "Okay." And waits for the next one.
    -> END
